'''Peider Lansel''' (August 15, 1863 – December 8, 1943) was a [[Swiss people|Swiss]] [[Romansh people|Romansh]] [[Lyric poetry|lyric poet]]. He is most known for having revived [[Romansh language|Rhaeto-Romansh]] as a literary language. His family was from [[Sent]], Switzerland, (although he was born in [[Pisa]]) and worked as a merchant, as well as being a poet.

