'''The Louis and Artur Lucian Award in Cardiovascular Diseases''' is a prize for cardiovascular medicine conferred by [[McGill University]]. Described as Canada's "top cardiovascular research prize",<ref name="Landau 2013">{{cite web | last=Landau | first=Elizabeth | title=Doctor is pain medicine 'visionary' | website=CNN | date=21 June 2013 | url=https://www.cnn.com/2013/06/21/health/garret-fitzgerald-aspirin/index.html | access-date=20 September 2018}}</ref> it has been awarded annually since 1978, except in 2007.<ref name="Genest Hébert Martin pp. 975–977">{{cite journal| last=Genest| first=Jacques| last2=Hébert| first2=Terence E.| last3=Martin| first3=James| title=The Louis and Artur Lucian Award in Cardiovascular Diseases at McGill University| journal=Circulation Research| publisher=Ovid Technologies (Wolters Kluwer Health)| volume=119| issue=9| date=13 October 2016| issn=0009-7330| doi=10.1161/circresaha.116.309972| pages=975–977}}</ref><ref name="CJC">{{cite journal| title=Fifty Years of Philanthropy: The Louis and Artur Lucian Award in Cardiovascular Diseases at McGill University| journal=Canadian Journal of Cardiology| publisher=Elsevier BV| volume=31| issue=7| year=2015| issn=0828-282X| doi=10.1016/j.cjca.2015.05.011| pages=949–954}}</ref>
